## 7. Test Architecture Notes

### 7.1 Why Two Copies of Extraction Logic?

| File | Purpose | Dependencies |
|------|---------|--------------|
| `src/{production_module}` | Production extraction | Full `src/` stack |
| `evals/eval_types/{domain}/pipeline_mirror.py` | Pipeline mirror | Zero `src/` dependencies |

`src/{production_module}` depends on the full project stack (config, schemas, external services). The pipeline mirror avoids that entire dependency chain so tests run without API keys. **Every pipeline-logic change MUST be mirrored in both files.**

### 7.2 Comparison Normalization

`compare_field()` in `runner.py` normalizes both extracted and ground-truth values before comparison: strip diacritics (NFD) → lowercase → collapse whitespace.

### 7.3 PII Masking

The eval runner masks sensitive fields to keep CI logs PII-safe:

```
# Raw value:    user@example.com   ->  Masked: u***r@example.com
# Raw value:    0912345678         ->  Masked: 091*****78
```

