### 8.2 Pre-Commit Hook Example

```bash
#!/bin/bash
# .git/hooks/pre-commit — block commits that break {domain} extraction

echo "Running {domain} eval tests..."
{all_tests_command}
if [ $? -ne 0 ]; then
    echo "ERROR: Tests failed. Fix before committing."
    exit 1
fi

{run_evals_command}
if [ $? -ne 0 ]; then
    echo "ERROR: Production evals failed. Fix before committing."
    exit 1
fi

echo "All {domain} checks passed."
```

